        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>adds triangles along the boundary to straighten it;</para>
<para>new triangle is added only if 1) aspect ratio of the new triangle is at most maxTriAspectRatio, 2) dot product of its normal with neighbor triangles is at least minNeiNormalsDot. Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::straightenBoundary</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>mesh</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>newFaces</computeroutput> defaults to a null pointer in C++. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
